org.elasticsearch.action.delete

Class DeleteRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.elasticsearch.common.ContextAndHeaderHolder
      • org.elasticsearch.transport.TransportMessage<TransportRequest>
        • org.elasticsearch.transport.TransportRequest
          • org.elasticsearch.action.ActionRequest<T>
            • org.elasticsearch.action.support.replication.ReplicationRequest<DeleteRequest>
              • org.elasticsearch.action.delete.DeleteRequest
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DocumentRequest<DeleteRequest>, IndicesRequest, HasContext, HasContextAndHeaders, HasHeaders, Streamable

    public class DeleteRequest
extends ReplicationRequest<DeleteRequest>
implements DocumentRequest<DeleteRequest>
    A request to delete a document from an index based on its type and id. Best created using Requests.deleteRequest(String).

    The operation requires the ReplicationRequest.index(), type(String) and id(String) to be set.

    See Also:
    DeleteResponse, Client.delete(DeleteRequest), Requests.deleteRequest(String)
